      "abstract": "The PHQ-9 is a 9-item self-report measure derived from the Patient Health Questionnaire that screens for and measures the severity of depression. Each item corresponds to a DSM-IV criterion for major depression. Items are rated on a 4-point scale (0=Not at all, 3=Nearly every day). The PHQ-9 is widely used in clinical practice and research.",
